{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Machine Learning Fundamentals\n\nThis notebook implements three classical ML algorithms from scratch using Maxima's numerics package. The **symbolic-numeric bridge** is the unique angle: we derive gradients symbolically with `diff()`, then evaluate them numerically — something that Python/NumPy cannot do in the same environment.\n\n1. **Linear Regression** — symbolic MSE gradient → numeric gradient descent\n2. **Logistic Regression** — symbolic cross-entropy gradient → binary classification\n3. **K-Means Clustering** — iterative centroid assignment",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 41,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Linear Regression\n\n### Symbolic Phase: Deriving the Gradient\n\nThe mean squared error loss for a linear model $\\hat{y} = a + b x$ is:\n\n$$L(a, b) = \\frac{1}{2N} \\sum_{i=1}^{N} (y_i - a - b x_i)^2$$\n\nWe use Maxima's symbolic `diff()` to derive the gradient analytically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Define the loss for a single data point */\nL_i(a, b, x_i, y_i) := (1/2) * (y_i - a - b * x_i)^2$\n\n/* Symbolic gradients */\ngrad_a_symbolic : diff(L_i(a, b, x[i], y[i]), a);\ngrad_b_symbolic : diff(L_i(a, b, x[i], y[i]), b);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 42,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "-y[i]+b*x[i]+a"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "-\\left(x_{i}\\,\\left(y_{i}-b\\,x_{i}-a\\right)\\right)"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 42,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The gradient per data point is:\n- $\\frac{\\partial L_i}{\\partial a} = -(y_i - a - b x_i)$\n- $\\frac{\\partial L_i}{\\partial b} = -x_i (y_i - a - b x_i)$\n\nSumming over all data and dividing by $N$ gives:\n- $\\nabla_a = -\\text{mean}(y - a - bx)$\n- $\\nabla_b = -\\text{mean}(x \\cdot (y - a - bx))$\n\nThe residual $r = \\hat{y} - y = (a + bx) - y$ appears naturally. In matrix form with $X = [\\mathbf{1}, \\mathbf{x}]$ and $w = [a, b]^T$: $\\nabla = X^T (Xw - y) / N$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate synthetic data: y = 2x + 1 + noise */\nn : 80$\nx_data : np_scale(6.0, np_rand([n]))$\nnoise : np_scale(1.5, np_randn([n]))$\ny_data : np_add(np_add(np_scale(2.0, x_data), 1.0), noise)$\n\nprint(\"Generated\", n, \"data points\")$\nprint(\"True parameters: a = 1, b = 2\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 43,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Generated 80 data points\nTrue parameters: a = 1, b = 2"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Build design matrix X = [1, x] of shape [n, 2] */\nones_col : np_reshape(np_ones([n]), [n, 1])$\nx_col : np_reshape(x_data, [n, 1])$\nX : np_hstack(ones_col, x_col)$\ny_col : np_reshape(y_data, [n, 1])$\n\nprint(\"Design matrix X shape:\", np_shape(X))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 44,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Design matrix X shape: [80,2]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Gradient descent using the symbolic gradient (now in matrix form) */\nw : ndarray([0.0, 0.0], [2, 1])$   /* initial weights [a, b]^T */\nlr : 0.01$\nmax_iter : 300$\nlosses : []$\n\nfor iter : 1 thru max_iter do block(\n  pred : np_matmul(X, w),\n  residual : np_sub(pred, y_col),\n  loss : np_mean(np_pow(residual, 2)) / 2.0,\n  losses : append(losses, [loss]),\n  grad : np_scale(1.0 / n, np_matmul(np_transpose(X), residual)),\n  w : np_sub(w, np_scale(lr, grad))\n)$\n\na_gd : np_ref(w, 0, 0)$\nb_gd : np_ref(w, 1, 0)$\nprint(\"Gradient descent: a =\", a_gd, \", b =\", b_gd)$\nprint(\"Final loss:\", last(losses))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 45,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Gradient descent: a = 0.6219872915418031 , b = 2.069644398527832\nFinal loss: 1.1755429181238"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Compare with closed-form least-squares solution */\n[w_ls, residuals, rank_X, sv] : np_lstsq(X, y_col)$\na_ls : np_ref(w_ls, 0, 0)$\nb_ls : np_ref(w_ls, 1, 0)$\nprint(\"Least squares:     a =\", a_ls, \", b =\", b_ls)$\nprint(\"Difference: |a_gd - a_ls| =\", abs(a_gd - a_ls),\n      \", |b_gd - b_ls| =\", abs(b_gd - b_ls))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 46,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Least squares:     a = 0.7445072224814612 , b = 2.038975333576846\nDifference: |a_gd - a_ls| = 0.12251993093965807 , |b_gd - b_ls| =\n                           0.03066906495098598"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot data and fitted line */\nx_list : np_to_list(x_data)$\ny_list : np_to_list(y_data)$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color = \"steelblue\", marker_size = 5,\n  points(x_list, y_list),\n  color = \"red\", line_width = 2, name = \"GD fit\",\n  explicit(a_gd + b_gd * t, t, 0, 6),\n  color = \"green\", line_width = 2, dash = \"dash\", name = \"lstsq\",\n  explicit(a_ls + b_ls * t, t, 0, 6),\n  title = \"Linear Regression: Gradient Descent vs Least Squares\",\n  xlabel = \"x\", ylabel = \"y\", grid = true, showlegend = true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 47,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "application/x-maxima-plotly": [
